  "texts": [
    "This works so long as the training data set is sufficiently diverse to learn these various features.",
    "An acknowledged limitation for this type of GAN is the correlation between the dimensionality of the input vectors (which increases with the number of features/objects to be modeled) and computation cost (including training time, hardware and energy consumed).",
    "To overcome this problem, conditional GANs (Wang et al. 2018; Odena et al. 2017; Sola and Gera 2023; Kang et al. 2023) have been introduced that condition the random input vectors on context-specific cues, such as object classes or scene descriptors.",
    "This is accomplished by inputting the additional information into the generator and discriminator, thus facilitating the generation of highly diverse content.",
